snippet.title: Web scammers go too far: They're using cute doggie pics
snippet.description: It seems the latest method to scam money from the innocent is to use cute doggie pics to entice vulnerable dog lovers.

snippet.title: AT-AT walker rocking horse built for little Sith lords
snippet.description: The fierce AT-AT walker from "Star Wars" gets a kid-friendly makeover as the world's geekiest rocking horse.

snippet.title: Woman wins competition, clones her dog
snippet.description: A British woman passionately needs her 12-year-old dachshund, Winnie, to be copied. So she wins a competition and a Korean company clones Winnie for free.

snippet.title: Fetch for iOS
snippet.description: Fetch is an entertaining adventure for both kids and adults alike, with colorful cartoon-like graphics, an extremely touchable interface full of little items to interact with, and challenging puzzles to solve as you explore a fantastical world.

snippet.title: WhatsApp: Facebook's Trojan horse for subscription services
snippet.description: WhatsApp's subscription business model may give Facebook hints about how to collect fees from users in its growing stable of social network services, instead of just relying on ad revenue.

snippet.title: Gears of War: Judgment (Xbox 360)
snippet.description: In Gears of War: Judgment, a few new gameplay mechanics and some fresh faces add some longevity to a series that has just about run out of gas on Xbox 360.

snippet.title: Disney uses the Force to snatch 'Star Wars' from Dark Horse Comics
snippet.description: Small world: After more than 20 years as the anchor of Dark Horse's empire of franchise comics, guess who'll be publishing "Star Wars" comics in the future?

snippet.title: LG Pocket Photo (Silver)
snippet.description: The compact and colorful LG Pocket Photo uses Zink technology and NFC communication to print out wallet-sized pictures from your LG smartphone.

snippet.title: Pinterest hacked with buttocks pics: Spam-butt suspected?
snippet.description: It seems that more than one Pinterest account was accosted by pictures of female rear ends and diet spam.
